This paper deals with the problem of identifying malicious web domains using machine learning techniques. The topic of cybersecurity and malware detection is closely related to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of machine learning algorithms to classify web domains based on their features and performance data falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of feature selection techniques to improve the performance of classifiers, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with the practical implementation of machine learning techniques for cybersecurity, which is a topic of interest in the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
